\sin\alpha=\frac{x}{Hypotenuse}
\cos\alpha=\frac{y}{Hypotenuse}
\sin^2\alpha+\cos^2\alpha=\frac{(x)^2+(y)^2}{(Hypotenuse)^2}=\frac{(Hypotenuse)^2}{(Hypotenuse)^2}=1
